Holotype SPAIN • 1 ♂ ; Salamanca , El Maíllo ; 40º33′24.8″ N , 6º10′23.9″ W ;
30 Mar. 2015
; A.R. Gonçalves and R. Andrade leg.; RBINS .

tp:treatment-sec.p:
WING. Stalk-like portion dark brown on basal half, pale on distal half (
Fig. 20G
).

LEGS. Black, except for yellowish to brown trochanters, knees and tarsomeres 1 and 2. Fore tibia with dense ciliation of long hair-like setae (distinctively larger than maximum diameter of tibia) with curved tips. Mid tibia anteroventral apical spur with distinct apical elongation (
Fig. 19I
), on basal half margin with 4 short, stout, curved spinose setae.

TERMINALIA (
Fig. 10
). Left epandrial lamella ½ shorter than left cercus, deeply bilobed. Left surstylus 2 times as long as wide.

Similar to male, except for following features: micropterous, wing round, brownish, bilobate, apical margin of each lobe bearing setae, posterior lobe with 1 long seta and the anterior with 3 short setae, both covered with grey microtrichia (
Fig. 20H
); legs covered with regular rows of setae; spur on mid tibia absent; cercus pale brown with grey microtrichia and setae; no longer setae on apical sternites.
